The '''1956 [[Oregon State Beavers football]] team''' represented [[Oregon State University|Oregon State College]] in the [[1956 college football season|1956 NCAA college football season]]. The Beavers ended this season with seven wins, three losses, and a tie. The team captains were Dick Corrick and Gerry Laird. The Beavers scored 203 points and allowed 166 points. Led by head coach Tommy Prothro, Oregon State won the Pacific Coast Conference championship and represented the conference in the Rose Bowl.
==Schedule== The Beavers finished the season with a 7&ndash;3&ndash;1 record, 6&ndash;1&ndash;1 in the Pacific Coast Conference. Ranks are based on the time the game was played.
